events.name: New York Knicks at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Julius Randle had 42 points and 15 rebounds as the New York Knicks extended their winning streak against the Detroit Pistons to 11 games with a 117-104 victory Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle's 42 leads Knicks to 11th straight win over Pistons

headlines.description: — Terance Mann slipped the gold-chained championship belt proclaiming “Big Moment Fella Performance” over his head.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mann, Leonard lead Clippers over last-place Rockets 121-100

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic matched a career high with 43 points and the Chicago Bulls snapped an 11-game losing streak against Golden State, beating the Warriors 132-118 on Sunday
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic helps Bulls snap 11-game losing streak vs. Warriors

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander and Josh Giddey each scored 28 points to lead the Oklahoma City Thunder to a 112-102 victory over the Brooklyn Nets on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giddey, Gilgeous-Alexander lead Thunder over Nets 112-102

events.name: Sacramento Kings at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes scored 29 points, Domantas Sabonis had 18 points and 18 rebounds, and the Sacramento Kings extended their winning streak to four games with a 132-119 win over the San Antonio Spurs on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings roll past Spurs, extend winning streak to 4 games

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic hit a go-ahead 3-pointer with 1.2 seconds remaining, capping his 12th triple-double of the season, and the Denver Nuggets won their 13th in a row at home by beating the Orlando Magic 119-116 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic's late 3 lifts Nuggets past Magic 119-116

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored 40 points and the Trail Blazers beat the Dallas Mavericks 140-123 on Sunday night, giving Portland consecutive wins for the first time since mid-December.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard nets 40, Trail Blazers complete 2-game sweep of Mavs

headlines.description: — LeBron James became the second player in NBA history to score 38,000 career points, but Joel Embiid had 35 points and 11 rebounds while the Philadelphia 76ers held off the Los Angeles Lakers 113-112 Sunday night for their seventh win in nine games.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron hits 38K, but Embiid leads 76ers past Lakers 113-112
